  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (97f070f 2023-03-17T09:32:25.079445775Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nSame error message as in https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/4572. While #4572 reported error when vm.rollFork is called within invariant test and was fixed, the same error still exists when vm.rollFork is called from a helper contract.\r\nWhen helperContract.rollFork is explicitly called, we get the panic.\r\nIf it is called by the fuzzer, no panic occurs but the fork block is not changed.\r\n\r\nPlease find basic setup and tests showing the bug in.\r\nhttps://github.com/Teamo0/FoundryRollFork",
